## Processing the migration plan

In `packages/blindfold/src/migrate.ts`, the code keeps a running set of environment variable names that were successfully sealed into the enclave:

```ts
const sealedVars = new Set<string>();

for (const item of plan) {
  if (item.action !== "seal") { results.push(item); continue; }
  try {
    await registerSecret({ name: item.sealName, fromEnv: item.envVar });
    sealedVars.add(item.envVar);
    results.push({ ...item, sealed: true });
  } catch (e) {
    results.push({ ...item, sealed: false, error: (e as Error).message });
  }
}
```

### Behavior

- Non-`seal` actions are passed through to `results` unchanged.
- For each `seal` action, `registerSecret({ name: item.sealName, fromEnv: item.envVar })` is awaited to push the secret into the TDX enclave.
- On success, the source `envVar` name is added to `sealedVars` and the result is tagged `sealed: true`.
- On failure, the result is tagged `sealed: false` and the error message is recorded; the variable is **not** added to `sealedVars`.

### Rewriting `.env`

After the loop, the code prepares to rewrite the `.env` file (creating a backup first), dropping or commenting out the successfully-sealed lines. The condition `if (sealedVars.size > 0)` guards this step so it only runs when at least one variable was sealed.

### Security property

This is the moment that closes the **one-file plaintext path**: secrets that lived as plaintext in `.env` are removed from disk (or commented out) once they have been sealed into the enclave via in-enclave substitution, so the running process must read them from the sealed store rather than from the on-disk file.

## Classification pipeline in `packages/blindfold/src/migrate.ts`

The migration command reads `.env` once via `readEnvVars(envPath)`, which returns `keys: string[]` and the raw `lines: string[]` — **values are never returned**, preserving the one-file-plaintext-path property.

### The four classifiers

```ts
const NEVER_SEAL = new Set([
  "T3N_API_KEY", "DID",
  "BLINDFOLD_MOCK", "BLINDFOLD_PORT", "BLINDFOLD_T3_ENV",
  "BLINDFOLD_DASHBOARD_PORT", "BLINDFOLD_BASE_URL",
]);

function isConfigName(k: string): boolean {
  return /(_HOST|_URL|_PORT|_EMAIL|_ENV|_REGION|_BASE_URL|_USER|_USERNAME)$/i.test(k)
    || /^(NODE_ENV|PORT|HOST|PATH|HOME|USER|SHELL|LANG|PWD)$/i.test(k);
}

function isAltT3(k: string): boolean {
  return /^t\d+_/i.test(k) || /_DID$/i.test(k);
}

function looksSecret(k: string): boolean {
  return /(KEY|TOKEN|SECRET|PASSWORD|PASSWD|PWD|_API|API_|_PAT|CREDENTIAL|ACCESS|PRIVATE)/i.test(k);
}
```

- `NEVER_SEAL` — hard blocklist of root creds (`T3N_API_KEY`, `DID`) and runtime config (`BLINDFOLD_*`) that must remain plaintext for the enclave to function.
- `isConfigName` — hosts, URLs, ports, emails, regions, base URLs, usernames, plus standard shell env (`NODE_ENV`, `PATH`, `HOME`, …).
- `isAltT3` — alternate Terminal 3 team keys (`t1_…`, `t2_…`) and any `*_DID` suffix; treated as root creds.
- `looksSecret` — positive detector for KEY/TOKEN/SECRET/PASSWORD/PWD/API/PAT/CREDENTIAL/ACCESS/PRIVATE patterns.

