const idNum = Number(contractIdArg);
```

### Attempted MapUpdateInput shapes
The `attempts` array enumerates six payloads, each tried in order against `tenant.maps.update("secrets", patch)`:
```ts
const attempts: Array<[string, unknown]> = [
  ["readers: only [<contract_id>]",        { readers: { only: [idNum] } }],
  ["readers: Only [<contract_id>]",        { readers: { Only: [idNum] } }],
  ["extraReadGrants: [<contract_did>]",    { extraReadGrants: [contractDid] }],
  ["extraReadGrants: [<contract_id_string>]", { extraReadGrants: [String(idNum)] }],
  ["readers: 'all'",                       { readers: "all" }],
  ["readers: 'All'",                       { readers: "All" }],
];
```
For each attempt it prints `→ trying <label>`. On success it logs `✅ accepted:` (truncated JSON), then advises `"Success — re-run \`npm run test:real\` to retry execute."` and returns. On failure it logs the error message (truncated to 240 chars) and tries the next shape. If all six fail it prints: `"None of the shapes were accepted. The maps.update RPC may use different field names than the d.ts suggests."`

