distinguishes a transport/grant failure (`host/http.egress_denied`, typically surfaced as an HTTP 500 from the T3 proxy when the enclave has not been granted egress to `HOST:HOST_PORT`) from a real contract bug. In other words, a `egress_denied` here means the in-enclave substitution path was never exercised, so the success-line guarantee (`sealed secret NEVER left the enclave`) cannot be made.

The script then finishes with `main().catch(...)` to surface any unhandled rejection from the whole flow.

